# Audit Policy API Testing (SITES-47306, SITES-48346)
# ====================================================
# This file contains HTTP requests for testing the Audit Policy API endpoints.
#
# Running requests:
# - IntelliJ IDEA / PyCharm: this .http format is understood natively by the
#   built-in HTTP Client - no plugin needed. Open the file and click the
#   green run arrow in the gutter next to any request.
# - Claude Code (CLI or desktop app): ask it to run a specific request from
#   this file (e.g. "run the 'Get current policy' request from
#   audit-policy.http") - it will translate the request + variables into curl.
#
# Auth: x-api-key is deprecated for this API starting August 2026. Get a
# ready-to-use session token via the mysticat CLI (no manual login-endpoint
# call needed):
#   mysticat login              # once, if not already logged in
#   mysticat auth token -e dev  # prints a session token - paste it below
# Paste the output into @sessionToken and skip straight to the POLICY
# section. (The optional LOGIN section further down calls POST /auth/login
# directly - only needed if you want to exercise that endpoint itself.)
#
# Environment: Update these variables for your environment
# - dev: https://spacecat-services--api-service.aem-dev.hlx.page
# - stage: https://spacecat-services--api-service.aem-stage.hlx.page
# - prod: https://spacecat-services--api-service.aem.hlx.page

@baseUrl = https://spacecat-services--api-service.aem-dev.hlx.page

# mysticat auth token -e dev
@sessionToken = YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN_HERE

# Dev test site: https://main--scope-creep--iuliag.aem.live
@siteId = 019ef3bd-5e67-7ea1-a4b7-f939f14fdc4e

# =============================================================================
# LOGIN (optional) - exercises POST /auth/login directly
# =============================================================================
# Only needed if you want to test the login endpoint itself rather than get
# a session token the quick way above. Get the IMS access token via
# `mysticat auth token --ims -e dev`, then copy "sessionToken" from the
# response below into @sessionToken above.

@imsAccessToken = YOUR_IMS_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accessToken": "{{imsAccessToken}}"
}

# =============================================================================
# POLICY - Read
# =============================================================================

### Get current policy (synthesizes version:0 defaults when none exists yet)
GET {{baseUrl}}/sites/{{siteId}}/audit-policy
Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}

### List policy revisions, newest first
GET {{baseUrl}}/sites/{{siteId}}/audit-policy/revisions
Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}

### List policy revisions with a smaller page size
GET {{baseUrl}}/sites/{{siteId}}/audit-policy/revisions?limit=5
Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}

### List the next page (replace with a "cursor" value from the previous response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/sites/{{siteId}}/audit-policy/revisions?limit=5&cursor=YOUR_CURSOR_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}

# =============================================================================
# EXCLUSIONS - Add & Remove
# =============================================================================

### Add exclusion globs
POST {{baseUrl}}/sites/{{siteId}}/audit-policy/exclusions
Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "values": ["/drafts/*", "/__e2e-audit-policy-test__/*"],
  "reason": "Excluding draft pages from audit scope",
  "note": "Requested by content team"
}

### Remove exclusion globs
POST {{baseUrl}}/sites/{{siteId}}/audit-policy/exclusions/delete
Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "values": ["/__e2e-audit-policy-test__/*"],
  "reason": "Cleaning up test data"
}

# =============================================================================
# INCLUSIONS (manual URLs) - Add & Remove
# =============================================================================

### Add manual URLs
POST {{baseUrl}}/sites/{{siteId}}/audit-policy/inclusions
Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "values": ["https://main--scope-creep--iuliag.aem.live/__e2e-audit-policy-test__/manual-page"],
  "reason": "Force-including a page excluded by sitemap heuristics"
}

### Remove manual URLs
POST {{baseUrl}}/sites/{{siteId}}/audit-policy/inclusions/delete
Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "values": ["https://main--scope-creep--iuliag.aem.live/__e2e-audit-policy-test__/manual-page"],
  "reason": "Cleaning up test data"
}

# =============================================================================
# AUDIT SCOPE - view stubs (501 until B4/B7 land)
# =============================================================================

### Get scoped pages (not implemented yet)
GET {{baseUrl}}/sites/{{siteId}}/audit-scope/pages
Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}

### Get scope summary (not implemented yet)
GET {{baseUrl}}/sites/{{siteId}}/audit-scope/summary
Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}

### Get scope sections (not implemented yet)
GET {{baseUrl}}/sites/{{siteId}}/audit-scope/sections
Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}

# =============================================================================
# ERROR CASES (for testing error handling)
# =============================================================================

### Missing auth (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/sites/{{siteId}}/audit-policy

### Non-UUID site id (should return 400)
GET {{baseUrl}}/sites/not-a-uuid/audit-policy
Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}

### Unknown site id (should return 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/sites/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/audit-policy
Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}

### Add exclusions missing reason (should return 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/sites/{{siteId}}/audit-policy/exclusions
Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "values": ["/no-reason/*"]
}

### Add exclusions with an empty values array (should return 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/sites/{{siteId}}/audit-policy/exclusions
Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "values": [],
  "reason": "test"
}

### Add an exclusion glob with a path-traversal sequence (should return 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/sites/{{siteId}}/audit-policy/exclusions
Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "values": ["../../etc/passwd"],
  "reason": "test"
}

# =============================================================================
# WORKFLOW: Complete Test Scenario
# =============================================================================
# Run these in order to test a complete workflow:
#
# 1. Login (exchange IMS access token for a session token)
# 2. Get current policy (note the baseline version)
# 3. Add exclusion globs (verify version bumped by 1)
# 4. Add manual URLs (verify version bumped by 1 again)
# 5. Get current policy again (verify both arrays reflect the additions)
# 6. List revisions (verify newest-first ordering, includes the two writes above)
# 7. Remove the exclusion globs and manual URLs added above (cleanup)
# 8. Get current policy once more (verify arrays are back to baseline)
